  <!-- What gets better -->
  <div class="py-20">
    <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: hsl(271 50% 55%)">What Gets Better</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">What changes when you do this work.</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">The inner critic quiets down</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Not disappears overnight, but loses authority. You start to recognize that voice as a remnant of the past, not the truth about who you are.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">Patterns start to shift</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">You catch yourself earlier. You have a beat of awareness before you do the thing you always do. That beat gets longer. Then something actually changes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">You stop carrying everyone else</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">You learn that your needs matter. That saying no is not selfish. That taking care of yourself is not the same as abandoning others.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">Your story becomes something you carry differently</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">The past doesn't disappear, but it stops carrying you. You understand it. You have compassion for the child who lived it. And you live less in it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

